ngs><font color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uieglios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ieglios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/8/01 6:02:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Something to enhance the RP environment</span><hr size=1>  Well met. I posted this similar idea on the developers corner a while back and wondered how the citizens of Norath here feel about them. First off I would like the ability for all priest classes(shaman,clerics,and druids) to convert(new skill or ability) agnostic players and add them to their god's flock. <br>
 Well, ok, so besides being able to where imbued or god specific items what good would that be? The next sugestion covers that. I believe that it would be possible to determine the number of each god's worshipers, in total and in each zone. The total number will determine the maximum bonus to each priests spell effects, with perhaps the dominant deities clerics gaining a special save modification to reflect that gods influence being superior to all others.It would work as a percentile based upon zone populations, the more followers grouped and in the same area the better the spell effects work and makes religion matter. <br>
 I would also like to see the ability to turn away from your deity(thus removing the benefits to all but preists who would not be allowed to). This is a very rough rendering and is just a sliver of where I would like to see it...I think there should be a difference between the priests of peace and the plaguebearer....as is they have all the same spells...why not throw some chanter mezzes to the priests of Quellious? Maybe some DOT disease spells for the priests of Bertox. Just a little bit of fleshing out would make soo much difference. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urhaxalygen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhaxalygen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/8/01 12:10:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_bigsmile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Something to enhance the RP environment</span><hr size=1> I would LOVE this, personally.  The gods are supposed <br>
to have sooo much influence in Norrath in the minds of<br>
the powers that be, but in actual game mechanics, a lot<br>
of people who can choose to be agnostic DO choose<br>
to be agnostic because of the easier faction handling.<br>
<br>
I recommend all your changes, plus these ideas:<br>
<br>
1.  Every god should have a special Bulwark like<br>
     Rodcet Nife does.  Each BP casts a special spell.<br>
     Quellious's might be Breeze, Bertoxx's Infectious Cloud.<br>
<br>
2.  Every god should have 3 Holy Symbols like Inny<br>
     does for their Clerics and Shamen to wear.<br>
<br>
3.  Every god should spawn in the game.<br>
<br>
4.  Every priest-class guild should have a Library Assistant<br>
     that hands out complimentary Lore (books, papers,<br>
     etc.), that give information about the god they follow and<br>
     stories about what each god has done in Norrath.<br>
     (Kind of like Deity Newspapers, with volume numbers.)<br>
<br>
5.  If you follow a deity, you should be allowed to do a<br>
     Disciple's Quest (similar to an Epic Quest, but very<br>
     deity-specific) and have a chance for an exaltation <br>
     into the Realm of Heroes or other grand advancement.<br>
     (For example, if you complete the Disciple's Quest <br>
      for Innoruuk, he will con Amiably to you always, <br>
      even if you kill stuff in his plane or kill him 8 times.)<br>
<br>
What do you think?  I think your ideas rock!<br>
<br>
Atrilinea <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwinglo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>winglo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=" http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_greenspot.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/8/01 12:44:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_bigsmile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Something to enhance the RP environment</span><hr size=1> <br>
