<br>
The history of Norrath already explains that the Gods have been mostly prevented from DIRECT intervention on the soil of Norrath because of previous wars waged by those Gods. Who did this? Nameless... the creator of the Gods.<br>
<br>
More spells and powers for a certain class or a certain alignment or a certain ethos has already been proven to NOT work in EQ.  Check out SZ server.<br>
<br>
Remember one SIMPLE fact..... EQ doesnt have a GM to directly interact with every player to prevent the total misuse of power. Another reason PvP doesnt work also. There is no means (at least none thought up yet) to make everyone play nice. No consequences of any real meaning to actions is bad for any situation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uieglios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ieglios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/9/01 4:30:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Something to enhance the RP environment</span><hr size=1> Direct combat between dieties has always resulted in Cataclysmic events however, the gods have and I suspect always will, dabble and interfere in the lives of their worshipers. It is logical also that the numbers of worshipers should have an affect upon the power of the god they serve, and that that influence should be used as rewards to those special mortals(priests) who spread the worship. Most RPG gloss over this in an attempt not to offend truely devote worshipers of true religions(oxymoron?) anyway it is interesting and definately something which makes sense from the game and a roleplay perspective. You should be able to change religions, perhaps convert NPC's(you can beg and steal from them so why not convert them) It would give the Charisma stat a real use for clerics. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uartillis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artillis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/14/01 5:36:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Something to enhance the RP environment</span><hr size=1> Interesting and nice idea, but verant dosn't let any one switch deities becase of the problems with correcting and changing factions in association to deities.  Supposedly it's to much of a programming pain becase of how many diiferent things in the entire game change just becase of who you worship in relation to quests, npc's liking or hating you and all that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uclanmcstump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ClanMcStump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/14/01 5:40:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Something to enhance the RP environment</span><hr size=1> I think faction changes upon converting would be a fairly easy fix... you become just above KOS to all factions relating to both your old and new god.  Your old god because you have &quot;fallen&quot; and your new god because you are new to the faith and not yet fully trustable.  Hell, maybe you should be KOS to all factions with your old god, you traitorous dog.<br>
<br>
Being able to convert NPC might be a bit out of the realm of possibility... but i think there should be an enchanter spell that allows them to grant &quot;auras&quot; of differant gods to players.  Might only last for a set time or last until you zone.  But would grant the player an amiable faction with the god<br>
<br>
Stemp McStump, Shifty-Eyed Bastard<br>
